    <note type="biography">
        <p>Portuguese-born English lawyer and politician. Conservative MP for South Salford, 1886–1900. Best known for courting controversy as a writer of political letters and historical treatises; also wrote extensively on ethnology. Wrote books arguing that violent floodwaters rather than glaciers were agents of geological change. FRS 1893.</p></note>
